{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> διφθέρα</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>prepared hide, piece of leather,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.194; ἐκ διφθερέων πεποιημέναι κυνέαι [prev. author] 7.77 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; διφθέραι, opposed to δέρρεις (hides), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.75 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a <b>drum,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Automatopoetica” 20.4; especially as writing-material, τὰς βύβλους διφθέρας καλέουσι ἀπὸ τοῦ παλαιοῦ οἱ Ἴωνες 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.58; δ. μελαγγραφεῖς 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 627 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. βασιλικαί, of Persian records, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Ctesias Historicus cited in 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. ἱεραί, at Carthage, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.942c\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; χαλκαῖ δ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 297a, cf. Scholia 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.175: proverbial, ἀρχαιότερα τῆς διφθέρας λέγεις 4th-5th c.AD: Diogenianus Paroemiographus 3.2 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; used for bindings, διφθέρας περιβάλλειν (i.e. βιβλίοις) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Ind.” 16. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>anything made of leather, leathern jerkin,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 72, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 53d, “SIG” 1259.6 (4th c.BC), 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 12, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tim.” 6, 38, 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Anabasis” 7.9.2, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; properly, <b>of goatskin,</b> opposed to μηλωτή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Ammonius Grammaticus “περὶ ὁμοίων καὶ διαφόρων λέξεων” p.44 V. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>wallet, bag,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.2.12, 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Orationes” 58.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>plural</i>, <b>skins used as tents,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.5.10, 3rd c.BC: Phylarchus Historicus 41 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6946","accentedUnicode":"διφθέρα","shortDef":"a leather covering","mediumDef":"a leather covering","stepGloss":"a leather covering","stepTransliteration":"difthera","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}